news.title: New home sales in USA drop 17.3% in October 2024
news.para: New home sales plunged 17.3% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 610,000 units last month, the lowest level since December 2022, the Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Tuesday.

news.title: Namma metro's delayed yellow line set to begin operations in January 2025
news.para: ​​Titagarh Wagons, the supplier, has been delayed in delivering the required trains. The company has assured that one set of six coaches will be handed over to BMRCL (Bangalore Metro Rail Corporation Limited) in December and another set in January, totalling 18 coaches.

news.title: Odisha: Buyers protest delay in OSHB’s Vasudev Vihar plot handover
news.para: The OSHB in May 2022 had advertised the scheme and named it ‘Vasudev Vihar', located near Kalinga Studio. It consists of 166 plots. The buyers, mostly retired employees, alleged that though OSHB took the entire money, it has not handed over the developed housing plots to them.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh's cantonment residents oppose MoD's land ownership clause
news.para: Manmohan Sharma, general secretary, HPCA, told TOI that the new clause, if implemented, would not change a thing for the cantonment residents, who have been struggling to get land ownership rights for decades.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA files six FIRs over illegal constructions
news.para: A senior Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) official said that the application to register three more cases was also sent to the police, and they will be registered soon.

news.title: Kochi’s green spaces vanish as urban areas double in 20 years: Study
news.para: ​​The findings reveal a 126% surge in built-up areas across the taluks of Kanayannur, Kochi, Kunnathunad, Aluva, and North Paravur between 2001 and 2020, far exceeding the global average of 20%.

news.title: Odisha government to amend real estate laws to ease sale deed registration
news.para: "Currently, there are some bottlenecks in the registration of sale deeds for apartments and land in the state and the govt is deliberating on bringing necessary changes to the laws and existing regulations," revenue and disaster management minister Suresh Pujari said on Tuesday.

news.title: Gurugram civic body authorizes zonal officers to correct property tax discrepancies
news.para: Joint commissioners were earlier authorised to handle assessment differences up to Rs 50,000. However, they can now manage cases with assessment differences between Rs 1 lakh and Rs 10 lakh.

news.title: Hyderabad Metro phase II to cover 76.4 km, fourth corridor put on hold
news.para: The phase 2 proposal, DPR, a comprehensive mobility plan (CMP), and also alternative transit analysis reports have been submitted to the Union ministry of housing and urban affairs (MoHUA) for technical and financial evaluation.

news.title: Survey to begin for Gurugram metro corridor linking Millennium City Centre & Cyber City
news.para: Gurugram Metro Rail Limited (GMRL) officials said on Tuesday that Systra India, appointed the detailed design consultant (DDC) for the project, will carry out a survey. It will take two to three months to complete.

news.title: Delhi civic body identifies 420 construction sites violating GRAP norms
news.para: MCD identified 367 sites measuring less than 500 square metres that failed to implement the specified dust control measures.

news.title: Punjab govt allows registration of small plots in illegal colonies without NoC for 90 days
news.para: The government has given 90 days to get the plots registered without NoC. However, it is not clear if owners would have to get NoCs issued from MC or Glada after the 90 days’ window.

news.title: SC upholds land acquisition for Yamuna Expressway development
news.para: The top court decided a batch of appeals and the cross-appeals filed by the landowners and the Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) respectively.

news.title: Noida authority files complaint with EOW against Logix Developers
news.para: Logix was allotted a 1 lakh sqm group housing plot on Apr 8, 2011 and the lease deed was executed on June 14, 2011.

news.title: Goa HC seeks govt replies on PIL against TCP development permits in private forest
news.para: The contour plan shows the number of villas on slopes as 1:4, which is not allowed under the TCP Act, he submitted. The drawings are prima facie manipulated, showing sections with very limited slopes partly going out, set aside, and not taking into account the actual steep slope areas, the petition stated.

news.title: NHAI awaits formal proposal for streetlights on Kazhakkoottam-Kovalam
news.para: ​​Streetlights have already been installed on the Karamana-Pravachambalam stretch under the Smart City initiative, following persistent demands from residents.

news.title: Avighna Group acquires Emaar Business Park for Rs 555 crore in Dubai
news.para: The Grade A commercial tower on prime Sheikh Zayed Road has a total 150,000 sq ft of office and retail spaces across ground plus six storey structure, leased to leading multinational and regional companies.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt plans 'New Agra' heritage city on Yamuna Expressway
news.para: Called ‘New Agra Urban Centre', the blueprint prepared by YEIDA envisages developing the new city mainly as a commercial and tourism centre on 10,500 hectares of land, which would make it roughly half the size of Noida.

news.title: Odisha HC orders bank to pay Rs 1 lakh compensation for delayed return of mortgaged property papers
news.para: Justice S K Panigrahi issued the direction in a case filed by a 70-year-old on Sept 24, in which he claimed the original documents were not returned to him by the bank "despite his persistence, including frequent personal visits and countless letters."

news.title: Uttarakhand CM's secretary orders investigation into land misuse in Kumaon division
news.para: Commissioner Rawat directed local sub-district magistrates (SDMs) and tehsildars to investigate cases in which land was bought for religious or agricultural purposes but was used for hotels, resorts, or other commercial spaces, noting that if any rules are violated, the land should be transferred to the state govt.
